I"o<p><strong>Ingreidents</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>200g plain flour</li>
  <li>150g wholemeal flour</li>
  <li>50g oats (I use 20g oats + 30g of seed mix) &amp; extra to sprinkle on top</li>
  <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
  <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li>
  <li>300ml neutral tasting dairy free milk</li>
  <li>1 tablespoon white wine vinegar or lemon juice</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Method</strong></p>

<p>Mix all dry ingredients together, then add milk (which has been curdled by previously adding white wine vinegar/lemon juice)</p>

<p>1lb loaf tin</p>

<p>Sprinkle oats / seed mix on top</p>

<p>Gas mark 5 for 40 minutes</p>

